# Backend API

- Mount routes under `/api/<resource>` in `app.ts`
- Router files: `src/routes/<resource>.routes.ts`, default export the router
- Keep `index.ts` for dotenv + listen only; export app from `app.ts`

```typescript
// routes/products.routes.ts
import express from "express";
const router = express.Router();

router.get("/", (req, res) => {
  res.json({ data: { products: [] } });
});

export default router;
```

- Use `express.json()` middleware (already in `app.ts`)
- Validate request bodies before business logic; return 400 with `{ error: { message, code } }`
- Use async handlers with try/catch; forward errors via `next(err)` when error middleware exists
